          "assignee": null,
          "assignees": [],
          "author_association": "OWNER",
          "body": "Filed from the pd-book-tools deep code/security review.\n\n    Report: `pd-book-tools/docs/research/2026-05-22-deep-code-security-review.md`\n    Finding: #18\n\n    ## Summary\n\n    Page.to_dict() emits provenance_live_ocr, provenance_saved_ocr, and provenance_saved as dicts, but the pydantic schema declares nullable strings.\n\n    ## Impact\n\n    Public wire format and pydantic/codegen contract disagree.\n\n    ## Evidence\n\n    - `pd_book_tools/ocr/page.py:2726`\n- `pd_book_tools/ocr/page.py:2728`\n- `pd_book_tools/ocr/page.py:2730`\n- `pd_book_tools/ocr/page.py:3557`\n\n    ## Acceptance\n\n    - [ ] Use nullable dict[str, Any] schema fields or narrow runtime fields to strings.\n- [ ] Add tests with dict provenance metadata.\n\n    ## Notes\n\n    This issue was filed from a read-only review. Confirm behavior with a focused failing test before implementation where practical.",
          "closed_at": "2026-05-22T16:04:15Z",
